{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Is Git?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Git is a distributed version control system. Every developer has a complete copy of the repository history on their machine \u2014 there is no single server that everyone depends on. Angular projects use Git for source control, and the Angular CLI automatically initialises a Git repository when you run ng new."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Git tracks changes as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "snapshots"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (complete file states at a point in time), not as diffs. Each snapshot is called a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "commit"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and is identified by a SHA-1 hash like "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "a3f5b2c"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Git three-area model: working directory, staging area, repository, remote"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Three Areas"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Understanding git's three-area model prevents the most common beginner confusion."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Area"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Contains"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to get there"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Working Directory"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Your actual files \u2014 what you edit in VS Code"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always the current state of the filesystem"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Staging Area (Index)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A prepared snapshot of selected changes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git add <file>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Repository (.git)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The permanent commit history"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git commit"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Changes must pass through the staging area before they become permanent. This lets you commit only part of the changes in a file, or group logically related changes together."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Initialising a Repository"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Create a new git repository in the current directory\ngit init\n\n# Create a new repository and clone it locally (typical for GitHub)\ngit clone https://github.com/myorg/my-angular-app.git\n\n# Angular CLI initialises git automatically\nng new my-app   # runs git init + initial commit internally\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core Workflow: Stage, Commit, Push"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Checking Status"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# See which files are modified, staged, or untracked\ngit status\n\n# Short format\ngit status -s\n# ?? = untracked, M = modified, A = added (staged), D = deleted\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Staging Changes"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Stage a specific file\ngit add src/app/app.component.ts\n\n# Stage all changes in a directory\ngit add src/app/\n\n# Stage all changed tracked files (not untracked)\ngit add -u\n\n# Stage everything (tracked + untracked) \u2014 use with care\ngit add .\n\n# Interactively choose which hunks to stage\ngit add -p src/app/app.component.ts\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Committing"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Commit staged changes\ngit commit -m \"feat(auth): add JWT refresh token support\"\n\n# Stage all tracked changes and commit in one step\ngit commit -am \"fix(api): handle null response from user endpoint\"\n\n# Amend the last commit message (only if not pushed yet)\ngit commit --amend -m \"fix(api): handle null response correctly\"\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Commit message convention: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Angular projects typically follow the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Conventional Commits"}, {"type": "text", "text": " spec: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "type(scope): description"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Types include feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore. This drives automatic changelog generation and semantic versioning."}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pushing to Remote"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Push to remote (first time \u2014 set upstream)\ngit push -u origin main\n\n# Push subsequent commits\ngit push\n\n# Push a new branch\ngit push -u origin feature/my-feature\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Viewing History"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Full log\ngit log\n\n# Compact one-line per commit\ngit log --oneline\n\n# Graph showing branches\ngit log --oneline --graph --all\n\n# Show changes introduced by a commit\ngit show a3f5b2c\n\n# Log for a specific file\ngit log -- src/app/app.component.ts\n\n# Last 5 commits\ngit log -5 --oneline\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branching"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branches are cheap in Git \u2014 creating one is instantaneous. Angular projects typically use a branch per feature, fix, or experiment."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch Commands"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# List branches (current marked with *)\ngit branch\n\n# Create a new branch\ngit branch feature/user-profile\n\n# Switch to a branch\ngit switch feature/user-profile    # preferred (Git 2.23+)\ngit checkout feature/user-profile  # classic form\n\n# Create and switch in one step\ngit switch -c feature/user-profile\ngit checkout -b feature/user-profile\n\n# Delete a branch (must be on a different branch)\ngit branch -d feature/user-profile   # safe \u2014 warns if unmerged\ngit branch -D feature/user-profile   # force delete\n\n# Rename a branch\ngit branch -m old-name new-name\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Branching Patterns for Angular"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch name"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Purpose"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "main / master"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stable, deployable code \u2014 protected on GitHub"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "develop"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Integration branch \u2014 merges from feature branches"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "feature/<ticket>-<desc>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "New Angular component, service, or feature"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "fix/<desc>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bug fix"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "chore/<desc>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dependency update, config change, CI update"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "release/<version>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Release preparation \u2014 version bump, changelog"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merging and Rebasing"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merging"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merging integrates changes from one branch into another. It preserves the full history of both branches and creates a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "merge commit"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Merge feature branch into main\ngit switch main\ngit merge feature/user-profile\n\n# Squash all feature commits into one before merging\ngit merge --squash feature/user-profile\ngit commit -m \"feat(user): add user profile component\"\n\n# Abort a merge with conflicts\ngit merge --abort\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebasing"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebasing replays your commits on top of another branch, producing a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "linear history"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Never rebase commits that have already been pushed to a shared branch."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Rebase feature branch onto latest main\ngit switch feature/user-profile\ngit rebase main\n\n# Interactive rebase \u2014 edit, squash, or reorder the last 3 commits\ngit rebase -i HEAD~3\n\n# After fixing conflicts during rebase\ngit add .\ngit rebase --continue\n\n# Abort a rebase\ngit rebase --abort\n"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": ""}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "History"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Non-linear (merge commits)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linear (cleaner log)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conflicts"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolved once"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolved per commit"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Safe to share?"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only if branch is local/private"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Angular project use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature branch -> main, PR merge"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Clean up before PR, sync with main"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Undoing Changes"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Discarding Working Directory Changes"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Discard changes in a file (restore from last commit)\ngit restore src/app/app.component.ts\ngit checkout -- src/app/app.component.ts  # classic form\n\n# Discard ALL working directory changes (dangerous \u2014 cannot undo)\ngit restore .\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Unstaging Files"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Remove a file from staging (keep changes in working dir)\ngit restore --staged src/app/app.component.ts\ngit reset HEAD src/app/app.component.ts   # classic form\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reverting Commits"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Create a new commit that undoes a previous commit (safe for pushed history)\ngit revert a3f5b2c\n\n# Undo the last commit but keep changes staged\ngit reset --soft HEAD~1\n\n# Undo the last commit and unstage (keep changes in working dir)\ngit reset HEAD~1\n\n# Undo last commit and discard all changes (DANGEROUS)\ngit reset --hard HEAD~1\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prefer git revert over git reset --hard for pushed commits. "}, {"type": "text", "text": "revert creates a new commit that safely undoes the change without rewriting history. reset --hard rewrites history \u2014 after a force push teammates who have already pulled will have a diverged history."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inspecting Differences"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Unstaged changes (working dir vs staging area)\ngit diff\n\n# Staged changes (staging area vs last commit)\ngit diff --staged\ngit diff --cached     # synonym\n\n# Difference between two commits\ngit diff a3f5b2c HEAD\n\n# Difference between two branches\ngit diff main feature/user-profile\n\n# Summary (file names only, not the diff content)\ngit diff --stat main\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Configuring Git"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Identify yourself (required before first commit)\ngit config --global user.name \"Your Name\"\ngit config --global user.email \"you@example.com\"\n\n# Set default branch name to main\ngit config --global init.defaultBranch main\n\n# Use VS Code as the diff / merge tool\ngit config --global core.editor \"code --wait\"\ngit config --global merge.tool vscode\n\n# Automatically set upstream on push\ngit config --global push.autoSetupRemote true\n\n# View all config\ngit config --list\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": ".gitignore for Angular Projects"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Angular CLI generates a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".gitignore"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that excludes node_modules, build output, and IDE files. Key entries:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Angular .gitignore (generated by CLI)\ndist/                   # build output\n.angular/               # Angular CLI cache (ngcc, incremental build)\nnode_modules/           # npm/yarn/pnpm packages\n*.js.map                # source maps (optional \u2014 some teams commit these)\n\n# OS\n.DS_Store               # macOS\nThumbs.db               # Windows\n\n# IDE\n.vscode/                # VS Code settings (commit .vscode/extensions.json, not settings.json)\n.idea/                  # IntelliJ / WebStorm\n\n# Environment\n.env\n.env.local\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Retrospectively ignore a file that was already committed:\necho \".env\" >> .gitignore\ngit rm --cached .env    # remove from git index (not from disk)\ngit commit -m \"chore: untrack .env file\"\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Working with Remotes"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A remote is a reference to another copy of the repository, typically on GitHub or GitLab. The conventional name for the main remote is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "origin"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git remote -v                    # list remotes and URLs\ngit remote add origin https://...  # add a remote\ngit remote set-url origin https:// # change remote URL\ngit fetch --all                    # download remote refs without merging\ngit pull origin main               # fetch + merge\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fetch vs Pull"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git fetch"}, {"type": "text", "text": " downloads remote refs without applying them. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git pull"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is fetch + merge. Prefer fetch + inspect before merging."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git fetch origin\ngit log HEAD..origin/main --oneline  # see incoming commits\ngit merge origin/main                # apply when ready\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tags"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tags mark specific commits \u2014 typically version releases."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git tag -a v1.0.0 -m \"Release 1.0.0\"  # annotated tag (recommended)\ngit tag v1.0.0                           # lightweight tag\ngit tag                                  # list tags\ngit push origin v1.0.0                  # push to remote\ngit push --tags                         # push all tags\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stashing"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git stash"}, {"type": "text", "text": " temporarily shelves changes so you can switch branches without committing."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git stash              # stash tracked changes\ngit stash -u           # include untracked files\ngit stash list         # list stashes\ngit stash pop          # apply most recent + remove from list\ngit stash apply stash@{2}  # apply specific stash\ngit stash drop stash@{0}   # delete a stash\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cherry-Picking"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "git cherry-pick"}, {"type": "text", "text": " applies a specific commit onto the current branch \u2014 useful for applying a bug fix from one branch to another."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git cherry-pick a3f5b2c           # apply one commit\ngit cherry-pick a3f5b2c..e8d4a1b  # apply a range\ngit cherry-pick --no-commit a3f5b2c  # stage only, don't commit\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolving Merge Conflicts"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conflicts occur when two branches change the same lines."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Conflict markers in a file:\n<<<<<<< HEAD\n  // your version\n=======\n  // their version\n>>>>>>> feature/user-profile\n\n# Resolve: edit file, remove markers, keep the correct code, then:\ngit add src/app/app.component.ts\ngit commit       # or: git rebase --continue\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conflict Prevention"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pull latest main before starting a feature branch."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keep feature branches short-lived to minimise divergence."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase onto main regularly to catch conflicts early."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Coordinate with teammates when modifying angular.json or app.module.ts."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Git Hooks"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Git hooks are scripts that run automatically at lifecycle events."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hook"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Runs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Angular use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pre-commit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Before commit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ng lint, prettier"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "commit-msg"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "After editing message"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Validate Conventional Commits format"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pre-push"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Before push"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ng build --configuration production"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "husky"}, {"type": "text", "text": " manages hooks as npm scripts, making them shareable through the repository:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npm install --save-dev husky\n# Add to package.json: \"prepare\": \"husky install\"\nnpx husky add .husky/pre-commit \"npm run lint\"\nnpx husky add .husky/commit-msg 'npx commitlint --edit \"$1\"'\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conventional Commits in Angular Projects"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Most Angular projects follow the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Conventional Commits"}, {"type": "text", "text": " spec: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "type(scope): description"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". This enables automatic changelogs and semantic versioning."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "feat(router): add route animations\nfix(forms): resolve ExpressionChangedAfterItHasBeenChecked\nrefactor(http): use functional interceptors\ntest(auth): add JWT refresh integration tests\nchore(deps): update @angular/core to 18.2.0\n"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "feat"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "New feature or Angular component/service"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "fix"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bug fix"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "refactor"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Code restructuring with no behaviour change"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph"